<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-11-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 330.</seg></opener>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <head><persName type="from">Mr. Fish</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                            Motley</persName></head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-11-17"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 17, 1870.</date></dateline></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Motley</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister</hi>,<hi rend="italic"> London:</hi></p>
                    <p>Send Sickles by mail and telegraph this. Your number 172 received. Course
                        fully approved. Insist firmly and vigorously on our plan for adjusting and
                        settling claims as shown in your note to Sagasta.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>FISH, <hi rend="italic">Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>